#: app/templates/faq.html:18 app/templates/faq.html:172
#: app/templates/help/getting_started.html:50 app/templates/index.html:23
#, fuzzy
msgid "What is Society Speaks?"
msgstr "Society Speaks について"

#: app/templates/faq.html:19
msgid ""
"Society Speaks is a civic technology platform that uses machine learning "
"to turn public participation into structured insight. We group "
"participants by how they vote — not by who they are — to surface "
"consensus statements (broad agreement), bridge ideas (ideas that unite "
"opposing groups), and genuine divisions worth addressing. It is open "
"source, ad-free, and free to use."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/faq.html:23 app/templates/faq.html:176
#, fuzzy
msgid "Is Society Speaks free?"
msgstr "Society Speaks"

#: app/templates/faq.html:24
msgid ""
"Yes. All core features are free: discussions, the Big Questions Journey, "
"the Daily Question, the Daily Brief, the News Transparency Dashboard, and"
" voting. A paid Personal Briefs subscription (from £4.99/month) is "
"available for those who want a custom daily digest from their own sources"
" — and it funds the free civic platform."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/faq.html:28
#, fuzzy
msgid "Do I need an account to use Society Speaks?"
msgstr "Society Speaks について"

#: app/templates/faq.html:29
msgid ""
"No. You can browse discussions, read the Daily Brief, and explore the "
"News Transparency Dashboard without an account. You do need an account to"
" vote on statements in discussions (so your progress is saved), create "
"discussions or programmes, or subscribe to the Daily Question by email."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/faq.html:33 app/templates/faq.html:199
#: app/templates/help/help.html:34 app/templates/index.html:39
#, fuzzy
msgid "What is the Big Questions Journey?"
msgstr "ビッグクエスチョンジャーニー"

#: app/templates/faq.html:34
msgid ""
"The Big Questions Journey is a guided civic experience covering the "
"issues that define our era. Each journey has 8 themes — climate and "
"planet, AI and technology, economy and work, health and care, war, peace "
"and security, democracy and institutions, society and cohesion, and "
"education and future skills — each starting with at least 7 expert-"
"curated policy statements. Participants vote on each statement and can "
"add their own. After voting, you see where you stand compared to others "
"and where society genuinely agrees, divides, and finds common ground. "
"Country-specific editions are available for the UK, US, Germany, France, "
"Netherlands, Ireland, Canada, Singapore, Japan, and China."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/faq.html:38
#, fuzzy
msgid "How many statements are in the Big Questions Journey?"
msgstr "ビッグクエスチョンジャーニー"

#: app/templates/faq.html:39
msgid ""
"Each edition starts with at least 56 seed statements — 7 per theme across"
" 8 themes. Participants can also submit their own statements, so the "
"total grows as the community contributes. Country editions reflect that "
"country's specific policy context and current debates."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/faq.html:43 app/templates/faq.html:230
#, fuzzy
msgid "What is the Daily Question?"
msgstr "デイリークエスチョン"

#: app/templates/faq.html:44
msgid ""
"The Daily Question is one carefully chosen civic question published each "
"day. You vote Agree, Disagree, or Unsure, optionally explain your "
"reasoning, and then see how others responded. Over time, this creates a "
"longitudinal record of how public opinion evolves on key issues. "
"Questions are delivered by email — weekly by default — and you can change"
" the frequency to daily or monthly in your preferences."
msgstr ""

